widgets_values:
# ControlNet ### Image Input - **Load CNet Image + Crop + Image Resize**
→ loads image and allows adjusting crop and size → right-click on **Preview Image** to queue and check the cropped/resized image

### Using Union/Promax ControlNet ? - allows switching between regular and Union ControlNet
→ **Sage Attention** does not work with the Union models
### SetUnionControlNetType - selection of ControlNet type
→ only when using Union ControlNet
### AIO Aux Preprocessor - choose **preprocessor** corresponding to selected ControlNet type
- **resolution** at which the input image is processed
### CNet for 1st/2nd Pass ? - allows targetting individual passes

nodes.title: ► INFO
widgets_values:
# IPA Control - allows targetting individual passes by passing through the regular **model** where set to **false**
→ This group should remain active at all times

W_target = a
H_target = b
W_input = c
H_input = d

# Check whether to pad horizontally or vertically; boolean (Wildcard * b/c BOOL != BOOLEAN)
pad_horizontal = True if (W_target > W_input) else False

# Width difference
W_diff = (W_target - W_input) / 2

# Height difference
H_diff = (H_target - H_input) / 2


return (pad_horizontal, W_diff, H_diff)

nodes.title: ► INFO
widgets_values:
# 1st Pass > regular sampling process with addtion of **Detail Daemon Sampler** - **daemon_detail_amount** → positive values leave some noise to turn into detail → negative values denoise more creating cleaner results

→ ***Detail Daemon Sampler** contains further settings for timing etc. to experiment with, but can generally be left alone.
Highlighted as a ♦️red node♦️ above the **SamplerCustomAdvanced***
- **Variation Seed Offset**
→ like the main **Seed Offset** this value is added to the **Global Seed** and the sum used internally
- **Noise Variation Strength** > Dials in the **Variation Seed** gradually. → a value of **0.00** will only use the main seed
→ a value of **1.00** will only use the variation seed

## CustomSamplerAdvanced > Serves as a live preview of the sampling process when **Preview Method** is enabled in the Comfy Manager.
To see the live previews rendered best, make sure to download the **TAESD** VAEs linked in the **resources** section.

nodes.title: ► INFO
widgets_values:
# Pass Input Hijack > Allows the **Input Image** to act as a specific Pass' result to prevent regeneration. → To use simply load a completed/saved Pass or copy/paste the clipspace directly into the **Input Image** > Specifically SVDQuant models can not reproduce a generation even with exactly matching parameters (*non-deterministic*).
For example locking all seeds in and tweaking only the ADetailer pass would result in all passes being rerun, with different results.
→ The Hijack can circumvent that issue

nodes.title: ► INFO
widgets_values:
# Inpainting - **Grow Mask**
– expands the provided masks
- **Gaussian Blur**
– blurs the mask for smoother integration
- **Crop Factor**
– multiple of the bbox area to be considered as context
→ usual range: 1.5 - 3.0
- **Feather**
– softens the crop's edges for a smooth result
– also functions as noise_mask_feather
- **Inpaint Size**
– temporary size of **Mask** area multiplied by **crop_factor** during generation
→ control over level of detail
→ disregarded when the masked area is larger already
- **Noise Mask** ■ **enabled**    → context aware    → smooth, seamless result ■ **disabled**    → ignores context    → allows forcing out of context content    → requires further measures to blend in smoothly (_i.e. more inpainting_)    → denoise acts like opacity


### DetailerDebug (SEGS) → for live-preview only, do not tweak

nodes.title: Inputs + Clipspace
widgets_values:
### Input Image > paste the image to be inpainted here ### Mask > paste the same image here and mask the inpaint area via **MaskEditor**   ► **MaskEditor (BETA)**
To mask an area, right-click on **"Mask"** and select **open in MaskEditor** from the context-menu
| ► **Controls** || | - | - | | alt + right-click-drag | brush size, brush hardness | | mousewheel | zoom | | mousewheel-click | pan image |   ### Copy - to copy an image's clipspace, right-click any "Preview Image" node labeled *(Clipspace)* and select:
→ **Copy (Clipspace)** ### Paste - to paste, right-click on the "Input Image" node and select:
→ **Paste (Clipspace)**
## Important > Do not copy the clipspace from the before/after compare nodes.

→ Pasted image clipspaces are temporary and might be gone next time ComfyUI is started or updated.

nodes.title: ► INFO
widgets_values:
# 2nd Pass ### Upscaling - **scale_by** – defines upscale factor (1.0 = **no upscale**)
- **Use Upscale Model ?** *(Ultimate Upscale always runs the selected model regardless)* **true** → uses selected upscale model **false** → regular upscale ### Sampling - **PAG** (Perturbed Attention Guidance)
→ similar to CFG; can enhance details greatly (0.0 = **off**)
- **daemon_detail_amount** → positive values leave some noise to turn into detail
→ negative values denoise more, creating cleaner results

→ ***Detail Daemon Sampler** contains further settings for timing etc. to experiment with, but can generally be left alone.
Highlighted as a ♦️red node♦️ above the **SamplerCustomAdvanced***
### Tiled Sampling - **tile_size + tile_overlap**
→ only applies when Tiled Diffusion or Ultimate Upscale is used
- **tile_batch_size**
– amount of tiles processed at once → reduce if low on VRAM
- **Use Tiled Diffusion ? + Use Ultimate Upscale ?**
→ regular sampling if both are set to **false**

**Tiled Diffusion**
→ faster
→ recommended denoise < 0.4

**Ultimate SD Upscale**
→ slower
→ recommended denoise < 0.3

### Color Correction > matches colors from previous pass - **strength**
→ 1.0 is usually good (0.0 = **off**)
### 2nd Pass — Tile ControlNet > helps keeping image composition intact when upscaling - **Note:** Union/Promax ControlNet does not work with SageAttention

nodes.title: ► INFO
widgets_values:
# ADetailer ### Detection - **bbox_detector** *(UltralyticsDetectorProvider)*
(e.g. "face_yolov8m.pt")
– detects bbox containing the part to be ADetailed
- **SAMLoader (Impact)**
(e.g. "sam_vit_b_01ec64.pth")
– segment-anything-model to crop the target part out of the bbox
- **segm_detector** *(UltralyticsDetectorProvider)*
(e.g. "person_yolov8m-seg.pt")
– detects the cropped out shape and masks correspondingly
- **BBOX Threshold**
– probability of the detected part to match the query - faces : detected reliably → higher values work well ~ 0.7 - 0.8 - hands : more difficult to distinguish → lower values ~ 0.4 - 0.5
- **BBOX Dilation**
– expansion of the detected bboxes
- **Crop Factor**
– multiple of the bbox area to be considered as context
- **Drop Size**
– size in pixels below which a detection will be disregarded
→ helps prevent after-detailing negligible background detections
### ADetailer - **Guide Size**
– size maximum for detections to be considered
→ allows skipping areas that are large/detailed enough already
→ disregarded when force_inpaint = **enabled**
- **Inpaint Size**
– temporary size the masked area is upscaled to during generation
→ control over level of detail
→ disregarded when the masked area is larger already
- **Feather**
– softens the crop's edges for a smooth result
– also functions as noise_mask_feather
- **Cycle**
– allows multiple iterative passes
- **Noise Mask** ■ **enabled**    → context aware    → smooth, seamless result ■ **disabled**    → ignores context    → allows forcing out of context content    → requires further measures to blend in smoothly (_i.e. more inpainting_)    → denoise acts like opacity
- **Force Inpaint**
– bypasses threshold and size criteria when **enabled**
Select the Wildcard to add to the text

# Seed values
global_seed = a
main_seed_offset = b

# 1st_Pass
input_width = c.shape[2]
input_height = c.shape[1]

# Upscale Factor
upscale_factor = d

# tile_size
tile_size = e

# tile_overlap
tile_overlap = f


# Calculate offset seed and modulus-clamp to a valid range
offset_seed = (global_seed + main_seed_offset) % 2**50


# UPSCALED DIMENSIONS
upscaled_width = input_width * upscale_factor
upscaled_height = input_height * upscale_factor


# OPTIMAL TILE CALCULATION
W = upscaled_width
H = upscaled_height

# UltimateSDUpscale
optimal_tile_width_USDU = 8 * ceil(W / (8 * ceil(W / tile_size)))
optimal_tile_height_USDU = 8 * ceil(H / (8 * ceil(H / tile_size)))

# Tiled Diffusion
optimal_tile_width_TD = optimal_tile_width_USDU + tile_overlap
optimal_tile_height_TD = optimal_tile_height_USDU + tile_overlap



return (offset_seed, upscaled_width, upscaled_height, optimal_tile_width_USDU, optimal_tile_height_USDU, optimal_tile_width_TD, optimal_tile_height_TD)
iif(max(a.width, a.height)>=max(b.width, b.height), max(a.width, a.height), max(b.width, b.height))

nodes.title: ► INFO
widgets_values:
# IPAdapter — General > *Utilizing the higher precision **IPAdapter ClipVision Enhancer*** ### ## Image Source - **IPA — Default Image Loader**
→ Loads images from the ```ComfyUI\input``` folder
- **IPA — Random Image Loader**
→ Allows randomized image loading from a path of your choosing
## IPAdapter ClipVision Enhancer > *This version of the IPAdapter is more accurate due to a tiling process, which analyzes images in multiple ClipVision passes to then funnel the embeds' values together into a more precise analysis result.* - input images should be square → cropped otherwise
→ **Image Resize** setting **method : stretch** can be used to squish images into squares without cutoff
- **Tile Amount**
– specifies amount of 224x224px parts the input is analyzed in
→ yields diminishing returns *(recommended value 3)*

nodes.title: ► INFO
widgets_values:
# IPAdapter — FaceID > *Specialized IPAdapter for facial resemblance* ### ## Image Source - **IPA — Default Image Loader**
→ Loads images from the ```ComfyUI\input``` folder
- **IPA — Random Image Loader**
→ Allows randomized image loading from a path of your choosing
## IPAdapter FaceID - input images should be square → cropped otherwise
→ preparing closeup reference images is highly recommended
- **Random Transform**
→ creates duplicates of the input with random rotations and hue-shifts, which helps the ClipVision pick up on features it may have missed otherwise

# Save Menu > enabling groups **Ⅰ- Ⅴ** saves images of respective pass with metadata - **Defaults** - **.webp** (lossless) → nth_Pass_timestamp - **.json** with the workflow data saved alongside - **save location** → "`ComfyUI\output\SDXL_Advanced`"

nodes.title: ► INFO
widgets_values:
# Advanced Settings
### Sage Attention Patch KJ - Enables/Disables SageAttention
→ requires [**Triton**](https://github.com/woct0rdho/triton-windows) and [**SageAttention**](https://github.com/thu-ml/SageAttention) to be installed
→ **not** compatible with : **Union/Promax ControlNet**, **SD15** models
### Alternative CLIP Loader > Allows loading in different finetunes for CLIP L and CLIP G ### Alternative VAE > Allows use of different VAE models, which mainly affect the generated images' saturation and contrast in a similar way filter adjustments would

nodes.title: ► INFO
widgets_values:
# LoRA Settings
### Accelerator + LoRA 1-6 - LoRAs are automatically appended to the positive prompt metadata
→ the **Accelerator** position at the top is not different in any way and only labeled out of personal preference
### Strength Sliders >Preset to the most common range of **0-1.0** - to enter specific values, double-click the number
- value ranges and steps can be tweaked within the **Properties Panel**
→ *(right-click context menu)*
- holding the **ctrl** key while pulling the slider against one of the edges allows exceeding the preset range

nodes.title: ► INFO
widgets_values:
## Positive Prompt (Wildcard-Support) - ways to prompt wildcards
• { option a | option b | ... }
• \_\_wildcard\_\_
• \_\_Folder\wildcard_in_folder\_\_
- wildcard file formats :
• **.txt** files within a folder hierarchy
• **.yaml** files for more complex structures
- default wildcard location *(Impact-Pack)* :
"`ComfyUI\custom_nodes\ComfyUI-Impact-Pack\custom_wildcards`"

→ can be changed by editing variable **"custom_wildcards"** in
"`ComfyUI\custom_nodes\ComfyUI-Impact-Pack\impact-pack.ini`"

nodes.title: Changelog
widgets_values:
## v10 - Structural changes - Addition of "Advanced Settings" to expand on the model loading options and allow use of custom CLIP models - Addition of ***Variation Seed*** feature to 1st Pass - Addition of **Pass Input Hijack** section allowing loaded images to act as 1st/2nd Pass result - Rework of Metadata collection - Rework of **LoRA Settings** group - Custom node pack changes : > **\-** : *ComfyUI-List-Utils*
> **\+** : *ComfyUI-Inspire-Pack*

nodes.title: ► Hello!
widgets_values:

nodes.title: ► General Info
widgets_values:
- Collapsed, nameless, black nodes can and should be ignored
- Optional, functionally unimportant settings will be mentioned and the nodes highlighted as ♦️red node♦️
- All ksamplers that are expanded only serve as a live-preview.
→ potentially exposed settings on them should be left alone
